[2026-05-22] HUMAN INTERVENTION - Friday morning recovery session begins

Context: Agent ran 25 iterations overnight (2026-05-21 to 2026-05-22), 
then stopped per the 5-consecutive-parse-failures rule in run_agent(). knit.py was written but agent did 
not measure test results because of the crash. final_report.md was empty because the parse-failure exit path 
did not call write_final_report() (known bug).

Diagnostics performed by human (no code/spec edits to artifact):

1. Ran the public test runner against current workspace/knit.py. 
Initial invocation failed with Windows path quoting bug ('python workspace\knit.py' got mangled to 'workspaceknit.py' by cmd.exe). 
Worked around by cd-ing into workspace/ before invoking with --compiler "python knit.py".

2. Subsequent run reported 0/150 with "stale expected output, regenerate" for nearly all tests. 
Investigated test_runner/run_tests.py is_stale_expected() function: it compares filesystem mtimes 
of .meta.json and .knit inputs vs .expected.json outputs. The cloned spec had .expected.json files with mtimes older than 
the .knit/.meta.json files (artifact of how the spec was extracted to disk), causing every test to be flagged stale before output comparison ran.

3. Touched all .expected.json mtimes to current time via PowerShell 
(Get-ChildItem -Recurse -Filter *.expected.json | ForEach-Object { $_.LastWriteTime = Get-Date }) to satisfy the harness's 
freshness check. No content modified, only filesystem timestamps. Verified by rerunning tests: real score reported as 11/150 with 
concrete output-mismatch failures.

[2026-05-22] HARNESS PATCHES (agent.py only, not knit.py)

Three patches applied to agent.py to address known limitations exposed by the overnight crash:

Patch 1: Increased call_model default max_tokens from 4000 to 8000, and updated the call site in run_agent. 
The overnight crash was caused by knit.py content (6KB+) wrapped in JSON envelope exceeding 4000 tokens, getting truncated mid-string, 
and producing unparseable responses.

Patch 2: Added write_final_report() call to the parse-failure exit branch in run_agent. Previously this exit path returned 
False without writing a final report.

Patch 3: Improved the parser-failure feedback message to the model, hinting at likely truncation and suggesting it split 
large files across two EDIT_FILE actions.

Committed as: "Friday morning recovery: bump max_tokens to 8000, write report on parse-failure exit, document intervention"

